Show Notes You can find Amir on Facebook at https: facebook. Impact Contact Home About Us Science Impact Contact Unlocking the power of the African Genome When compared to all other populations combined, the African genome is the most genetically diverse in the This diversity holds significant potential for the healthcare of Africans and the entire Learn How Our Purpose Committed to Global Health We are an African genomics research, services and development company addressing the need to include African genomic data in research which could lead to medical breakthroughs and new healthcare solutions Through our research collaborations and commercial partnerships, we will enable the study of African genetics to learn the underlying genetic drivers of disease affecting everyone Additionally, we strive to understand the genetic impact on disease penetrance and risk in Africans with a goal of developing better diagnostic and risk assessment tests to inform a more targeted approach to Learn More Our Goal Our Leadership Our Values Our Culture Science Driven to Develop Better Insights Many new drugs and diagnostic products are being made without the inclusion of African genetic This runs the risk of medicine and other health products being less efficacious in people of African descent and could also mean that revolutionary drug targets are To solve this problem, we collaborate with African researchers and research institutions to generate primary data to promote research and development while growing As part of our research collaborations, we collect clinical data and generate genetic data on the African population which may be utilized in global genomics research to produce novel insights in the discovery of drugs that are more effective on Africans and the global Learn More In the News Nigerian startup launches genomics Fund | Collab Capital Home Fund Fund Overview FAQs for Investors FAQ for Founders Studio About Contact Select Page Fund A capital solution designed to capture value missed by existing financial products Creating a New Institution Collab Capital is an investment fund leveraging financial, human, and social capital to help founders build sustainable, technology enabled We create growth opportunities for Black founders with startups by providing investment capital and connecting them to corporate and or social Through our investment programs we guide portfolio companies to increased revenue and profitability instead of continuously raising valuations through modern venture capital Return Capital Sooner As part of our solution we implement profit sharing once the company reaches predetermined revenue This allows us to offer our investors earlier access to returns without forcing a sale, IPO or crippling the Long Term Upside While we offer creative ways to generate and return our investors’ capital, we also retain an equity stake to protect our upside in the event of an acquisitions, merger or Explore the financials with our Return Calculator . Our goal is to create, grow, and sustain wealth in the Black community by building successful , companies through effective connections between Black innovators, investors and Want more on how we re investing in Black businesses? Receive Updates Connect with COLLAB We re ready to learn how we can work together!   Northyards Blvd NW Suite Atlanta, GA Twitter Instagram Made with Love in Atlanta   Investor FAQs | Collab Capital Home Fund Fund Overview FAQs for Investors FAQ for Founders Studio About Contact Select Page Investor FAQs We’re doing something new and know you have Here are few answers! How often will investors see returns? Though there is no perfect answer to this question, we are looking to deliver returns to investors within the first months of capital Do I need to be an accredited investor to invest in the fund? An accredited investor is a person or entity who is allowed to deal, trade and invest in financial securities as long as they satisfy one (or more) requirements regarding income, net worth, asset size, governance status or professional What are the investment criteria for the fund? Our investment matrix is one of the areas that make Collab Capital We follow a set of investment benchmarks but at a minimum our investments must meet the following criteria Minimum Requirements A business owned by % or more by a Black founder Tech, tech enabled, or innovative company with revenue growth potential of at least $10M Collab Capital is able to provide value and resources Founder attributes of a heart for community impact and a desire for ownership optionality Collab Capital evaluates and invest in businesses with revenue growth over a minimum of 3 month Desired Minimum of $10K MoM in Revenue with potential realization of ROI in within the first 1 to 3 years of investment How does Collab Capital identify potential investments? At Collab Capital we look for 3 key things First we look for companies and founders working on innovative solutions in niche or growth Second, we look for companies with revenue and are tracking towards in annual Additionally, we want to ensure that we can see a path to in annual Finally, while placing the company’s financials in our proprietary calculations, we look to ensure that our model is a good fit for their business model and Though we will always remain opportunistic we want to ensure that our model meets the needs of the founder and their desired path of For more information on investment criteria please see the “What are the investment criteria for the fund” FAQ How does this portfolio differ from other funds? Because Collab Capital has identified a massive gap, and consequently an opportunity, in the funding market we have created a new approach financial product to close the This solution to this identified gap and leveraged networks of the founders has often and continues to find the best companies to invest in Are there investments Collab Capital will not make? Our investment framework is based on impact and guided by the redemptive investment We see a lot of potential for our model in direct to consumer companies and enterprise We’ve also seen early signs of potential in tech enablement and productivity Finally, we won’t invest in industries businesses that require long research periods or changes to policy for the product to eventually “fit” a These include biomedical, advanced hardware electronic devices (think a new automobile) and aerospace transportation (trains rockets etc.) Additionally, our investments will be, in many ways, reflective of what we (the General Partners) collectively believe How much are the General Partners investing in the fund? Collab Capital General Partners will invest 2% of the Can an LP invest as an individual or as a company? Collab Capital does not provide a vehicle for individual investors

Science - Neumora Skip to main content About Science Patients Pipeline Careers News Contact Science Redefining neuroscience research & development by tackling the brain disease heterogeneity problem Brain diseases, such as Depression, Schizophrenia, Alzheimer’s, and Parkinson’s, are comprised of highly heterogeneous patient These conditions are driven by multiple, complex disease drivers including genetics, biological pathways, and environmental However, people living with brain diseases are diagnosed with broad disorders, defined primarily by subjective clinical symptoms, rather than genetics and biological Treatments are not targeted and may work for one patient but not the This traditional “one-size-fits-all” approach leads to underwhelming efficacy and routine clinical trial It is time to think differently and take a more precise Learning from the revolution in precision oncology, we aim to overcome the historical challenges of drug development for brain diseases by developing precision To develop targeted medicines, we need to deeply understand the multiple drivers of brain Instead of taking brain biopsies, our solution is to develop proprietary Data Biopsies™ by integrating multiple data types to provide a more complete picture of the specific mechanisms that drive brain diseases in specific patient Our Solution: Data Biopsy Signatures™ To cut through the heterogeneity of neuropsychiatric disorders and neurodegenerative diseases, Neumora’s scalable data sciences platform is designed to identify and define patient subtypes by mapping the mechanisms that drive brain diseases through the development of Data Biopsy We then map the underlying disease mechanisms as described by the Data Biopsy Signature to a Precision Phenotype™, which defines the clinically relevant characteristics of distinct patient Instead of the current broad classifications of brain diseases, Precision Phenotypes are driven by a deep understanding of the underlying disease, leading to novel target discovery and enhanced clinical trial This precision approach enables us to deconvolve the complex systems that drive brain diseases and match the right patient populations to targeted Prospective patient enrichment and selection will increase the probability of success and efficiency of drug development for brain diseases as we aim to improve treatment Our courtesy of NASA Archives I’m fortunate to be involved in a few awesome Like clockwork, every few months a Data leader will pop up asking for advice on how to calculate the for their The question is usually in the context of a budget decision, where they need to justify expanding headcount or purchasing a new The name has been changed to protect the innocent While there’s a subtle irony in the team responsible for quantification struggling to quantify their work, calculating a true “ROI” can be challenging because of the way data teams typically In some cases, the data team has a impact that can be directly For example, if the company sells data as their product, the Data team has a clearer, more obvious connection to value But for most teams, their impact is created indirectly: they are partners, acting in support of functions like Marketing, Operations, or Engineering to affect company In organizations like these, efforts for the Data team to come up with a standalone ROI will be underwhelming and Calculating a crisp “return” on an analysis project or model is difficult, and it’s even harder for infrastructure investments: how do you quantify the impact of a better schema, or a more reliable pipeline? Product Home Products Careers Contact Sales Metrics without Compromise The Problem As enterprises prepare for a cloud native world, there is a major transformation in technology There is a migration from large monoliths to small microservices along with a migration from physical servers to VMs and now Not only are there many more components, but the number of relationships between these components have exploded This all leads to systems that are increasingly difficult to monitor due to the increased complexity and amount of monitoring data being None of the existing tools today are equipped to even store the vast amounts of data being produced, let alone make use of The Solution The Chronosphere platform is an end to end monitoring platform purpose built for enterprises as their technology stacks evolve for a cloud native Having built M3 in open source to solve this problem for themselves, the team at Chronosphere is now Â bringing the solution to enterprises Use Cases Infrastructure Monitoring Monitor every component of your infrastructure, from containers to VMs to physical servers and network Application Monitoring Monitor every one of your microservices, the relationships between them and the dependencies between your applications and Business Monitoring Monitor your top line business metrics and drill down to the underlying applications and Unlimited Scale and Performance The Chronosphere team were the original creators and maintainers of the open source metrics platform, M3, which is used to power the Chronosphere platform The team has scaled M3 up to one of the largest metrics systems in the world and with no sign of slowing down, it is guaranteed to scale up with your Scale is great, but scaling without controls can be Chronosphere adds enterprise focused features to M3 such as intelligent rate limiting and security and access control such that all teams within your organization can leverage the power of a single centralized platform, with fine grain controls, resource limitations and Highest Levels of Reliability The Chronosphere platform has been battle tested in production for years while running one of the worldâs largest monitoring It has maintained the highest levels of reliability during that time and the same team can now run the same platform for you and your Each configuration provides an increasing level of reliability, but comes at varying Chronosphere puts that choice in your hands so you can pick what is best based on your Low Costs and Efficiency Controls When dealing with scale and large amounts of data, cost quickly becomes an Luckily, Chronosphereâs users do not have to compromise on that Chronosphereâs underlying technology has been proven by multiple users to be an order of magnitude more cost efficient than their legacy Additionally, Chronosphereâs product comes with efficiency controls built This means that you can control both the level of detail you want to store your data in as well as the length of time you would like the data to be retained This can be configured in a uniform policy across all of your monitoring data or just a select subset of your Automated Data Utilization Chronosphereâs product comes with visualization and alerting capabilities that are specifically designed to utilize the sheer amount of data being produced and These capabilities come with a focus on data recognition and automation as manual configuration does not scale when we are dealing with tens of thousands of dashboards and millions of Open Standards Compatibility Being built on an open source product, Chronosphere strongly believes in open source standards and building transferable This is why the platform supports all the standard CNCF open source metric ingestion formats such as StatsD, Carbon and Prometheus as well as all the standard open source query languages such as PromQL, Graphite and With such a wide range of open standard support, you are not locked Proofs (zk-Proofs) were known long before blockchain technology emerged but with distributed ledgers, a whole new set of possible came Simply speaking, a Zero Knowledge Proof lets you prove to a verifier that you know something, without revealing that Here is an intuitive, example of what this might look A seeing person is the prover, a blindfolded person is the verifier, and there are two balls of different The seeing person (prover) wants to convince the blindfolded person (verifier) that the two balls are of different colors, without revealing the They sit down at a table and the blind person shows the prover one of the The blind person continues to put both balls under the table and chooses to show one ball in a second round - either the same one as before or the other If he chooses to show the same ball, the prover knows because he sees the same color and he tells the blind If the blind person were to show the other ball, the prover could tell with certainty that the verifier (blind person) switched the balls under the In the second round, the prover would have a chance of getting the right answer if they had to They would have to guess in case the claim that they are trying to prove (the balls are of a different color) was At this point, the blind person cannot be sure if the claim is correct, or if the prover got If they repeat the game several times, the chance of getting the answer right every time through guessing decreases After just ten rounds of the game, the chance of calling the right ball every time through pure luck has decreased to 1 in (1 2^10). The blind person can be pretty sure by now, that the two balls are of different colors although the prover has not shared any information about the colors The idea of using Proofs for cryptocurrency transactions is the following: You construct a proof that the transaction you want to send would be considered valid by a verifying node without revealing any of the actual transaction This allows the sender, receiver, and the amount to remain Another that is perfect for the application of is identity you can prove to an entity that you are of a certain age without revealing any personal data like your Find out more Blockchain Elements A hash function is a mathematical function with a few special properties but like any other function, it does one The hash function takes an input and produces an output (also called hash value, hash digest or a hash). keep reading Blockchain Protocol A protocol is a standard composed of a set of rules and conventions used for a given Let us take a look at what some of the conventions and rules for a blockchain look keep reading Directed Acyclic Graphs The term DAG stands for Directed Acyclic The structure on the far left of the image below is a simple graph made up of nodes and edges connecting th

CIÊNCIA DE DADOS ESTÁ EM NOSSO DNA Estamos construindo um mundo mais inteligente, produtivo, econômico e confiável Dados estão em todos os lugares e entender o que eles querem nos dizer não é uma tarefa fácil Depois de trabalhar em conjunto com a Klabin por 2 anos, antes mesmo de criar a Tractian, começamos a ir para o mercado com parte da nossa solução existente Fazendo isso identificamos um grande problema em oferecer apenas um Saas para a indústria brasileira: grande parte da indústria ainda não tem a base com hardware e sensoriamento suficiente para começar a monitorar seus ativos e sofrem com as quebras repentinas causadas por ineficiência em medir a saúde do Além disso, os que já fazem bem o sensoriamento do ativo, não conseguem ir muito além de manutenções periódicas e ainda assim sofrem com quebras Principalmente por contar apenas com o fator humano, que utiliza de um supervisório para detectar o mal funcionamento das Causando grandes prejuízos para a indústria que não sabe de forma antecipada que algo irá quebrar e se submete a parar o processo produtivo para substituição de Além do setor industrial, grande parte dos fornecedores de equipamentos, principalmente os pautados em um modelo de negócios de Maas (Machine as a Service), passam pelos mesmos problemas mas em um nível acima: quando um equipamento alugado para de funcionar no cliente, a cobrança por velocidade na troca acaba aumentando os gastos por equipamento Causando insatisfação no cliente e possível rompimento de contrato de fornecimento de Para os fornecedores, não saber com precisão a saúde do ativo, impossibilita fazer uma gestão de estoque mais otimizada e manutenção preventiva Tudo isso aumenta os gastos com números de equipamentos parados em estoque e impede o atendimento de mais Folha Vitória Mais sobre nossa história Foi tentando solucionar esses problemas milionários que os engenheiros Igor Marinelli e Gabriel Lameirinhas fundaram a Tractian, uma startup que utiliza as tecnologias de maior destaque na atualidade–inteligência artifical, machine learning e internet das coisas– para analisar a saúde de máquinas e equipamentos e prever com uma significativa antecedência qualquer Veja a notícia É preciso desafiar o que parece ser impossível e MUDAR TUDO QUEBRA DE EQUIPAMENTOS As falhas se tornaram Nós devemos aprender com o fracasso e para orientar nossas próximas Introducing Infinitus Success Stories About Us Careers Blog Login Request Demo July 1, Introducing Infinitus Ankit Jain Infinitus CEO Today, my Shyam Rajagopalan and I are introducing the world to Infinitus, a voice robotic process automation (Voice RPA) company targeted to reduce the complexity and cost of healthcare in the United We have been working on this project since February and are excited to share our progress on it on this blog over the coming Healthcare is one of the most important sectors, but has lagged others in My wife has worked in healthcare operations for the last ten years and has repeatedly complained about the fact that at the root of most healthcare infrastructure problems, is a lack of data interoperability, with most data being communicated via disparate portals, faxes or voice phone This lack of interoperability is at the heart of the problem we are aiming to solve at In fact, over million phone calls occur every year in the US alone where the primary purpose of the call is to initiate a process, collect information, request clarification, or check the status of a previously initiated The average phone call is over minutes in length, and over a million healthcare professionals spend over hours each day making these tedious phone Recent advances across speech to text, dialog engines and speech synthesis have made delivering the pipe dream of an intelligent conversational engine a The large technology players have shown the promise of such technology for consumers across platforms like Alexa, Siri and Google The Infinitus platform is using these breakthroughs to fix the healthcare interoperability Shyam describes a number of the technology breakthroughs we have brought together to make our system possible in this blog post In recent years, robotic process automation (RPA) has taken business transformation teams by storm, and rightfully Companies like UIPath, Automation Anywhere, and Olive are helping teams that do tedious and repetitive tasks use technology to mimic human actions and automate However, these technologies are limited by actions that can take place on a Given the analog methods of communications in healthcare, traditional RPA breaks down when a workflow requires an offline action like sending or receiving a fax or a phone This is where we knew we could make a difference with The Infinitus platform automates, and helps our customers automate, outbound phone There is an extreme shortage of healthcare professionals and those in front and back office settings are often juggling multiple tasks just to keep things We believe that technology can and should augment these teams, so they can spend less time on calls and devote more time to patient We believe that our solution can reduce time to therapy for patients and reduce the number of administrative errors that generate throughout the Finally, we provide elasticity in a field that has traditionally been dependent on the massive scaling of human workforces to deal with sudden or seasonal Our system is in dire need of solutions that drive better health outcomes while reducing overall I couldnât be more proud of our team which has worked tirelessly over the last months to serve the needs of over healthcare We are deeply indebted to our early customers and partners who have not only helped us shape our platform, but also helped us understand the gravity of the problem that we are Finally, we couldnât have done this without our investors who have trusted us not only with their time and money, but also with the freedom to explore and build a solution to a problem that is both gnarly and omnipresent in the world of We are growing our team across the San Francisco Bay Area, Phoenix and the Great Denver metros and have a number of open positions . If you would like to join a team that is driven to structure the worldâs communication, starting in healthcare, and make interoperability effortless, please do apply and we look forward to getting to know Last Blog Post Conal: NLU at Infinitus Next Blog Post Technology at Infinitus Related Blog Posts July , | By Shyam Rajagopalan Technology at Infinitus In this post, I outline some of the breakthroughs we have had to make and preview some of the exciting technical challenges that lay Read More July , | By Conal Sathi Conal: NLU at Infinitus This week, weâre excited to be featuring Conal Conal has been building the computer brains that drive the conversations that the Infinitus digital assistant From rule based systems to models, Conal has been pulling out all stops to make sure our customers are getting the most out of their Infinitus Read More July , | By Diana Jung Diana: Engineering at Infinitus This week, weâre excited to be featuring Diana Diana has been focused on automation tools at She has been rethinking how data labeling tools in the conversational AI world should be Read More July , | By Brad Holden Brad: Operations at Infinitus This week, weâre excited to be featuri

Our Project in Hawaii – Terraformation Skip to content Terraformation Our Project in Hawaii Posted by Yishan Wong Posted in Uncategorized Tags: Climate Change , Reforestation In considering strategies to fix climate change, it turns out that the , , and most politically feasible strategy is the massive global reforestation of 3 billion acres . To concretely prove out key technologies and costs, we have recently completed construction of the world’s largest fully % desalination There are other larger desalination plants, but they are all and or reliant at least partially on fossil In contrast, we are completely independent and % powered by solar Our facility comprises a half of solar panels rated at roughly kW total generating power and kWh of battery It is designed to produce ,000 liters day (34,000 gallons day, or m3 day) of freshwater, more than enough to irrigate the entire The facility is off the grid, so we have created our own electrical and water Recent cost improvements in solar mean that green desalination is now The significance of this cannot be understated, because desalination is uniquely suited to using solar power, as it avoids the solar intermittency issue . The area of North Kohala where our project is located used to be covered with an ancient sandalwood forest, from the mountains to the Hundreds of years ago, the entire forest was cut down to supply the profitable sandalwood trade and the region never It remains a desert to this As of December , we have been working on this project for about 2 years and have reached the final phases of full integration We’ve produced hundreds of thousands of gallons of freshwater and begun to regreen the surrounding land, and have begun the planting of anchor tree Our facility is located on the Big Island of Hawaii, where the freshwater now enables us to begin restoration of the lost sandalwood forests on the western slopes of the Kohala Biomes are If you deforest a region and make it a desert, it stays a If you reforest a region, it will actually sustain itself too: plants cool the atmosphere and bring This means that if we can reforest a region and irrigate it until the trees are mature, we can a Our project is just a small beginning within the entire North Kohala Successfully reforesting this part of it would show that it can be done — not just here, but in deserts and other marginal land around the There have been many projects over the past few decades where determined individuals or communities were able to reclaim a The technologies we are employing here demonstrate a full system that can be replicated Reforestation aided by irrigation is likely to be the and method of mitigating or reversing the effects of climate change at It can be done by communities and people everywhere, and in a very decentralized If you are in the area and would like to drop by for a tour or have any questions, please contact us at . Reposted from Medium: https: medium.com @yishan our-project-in-hawaii-4c6c5a6052d7 Share this: Twitter Facebook Like this: Like Posted by Yishan Wong Posted in Uncategorized Tags: Climate Change , Reforestation Post navigation Previous Post Previous post: A Massive Global Reforestation Project Is How We Fix Climate Change Next Post Next post: Frequently Asked Questions Terraformation , %d bloggers like this:   Reforestation – Terraformation Skip to content Terraformation Reforestation at Future Forests Future Forests reforestation site Future Forests is a reforestation site in the Kona The site is a remnant dry forest that has been degraded over time by human habitation and There are some important native species that comprise the dry forest still present here and we are expanding the project around those The challenge of this site is Leucaena leucocephala , haole koa, which was brought to Hawaii in the ’s as cattle It is native to Central America and is an invasive species in Hawai’i, forming monotypic stands and pushing out native The low green plants in this picture are thousands of small haole koa seedlings that have to be constantly eradicated so native plants can be planted to rebuild the dry Services Provided Land Preparation Planting Seed Banking Plant Survival Monitoring Let’s work together Name (required) Email (required) How can we help your forestry project accelerate or get started? Submit Share this: Twitter Facebook Like this: Like Terraformation , %d bloggers like this:   Tree Nursery – Terraformation Skip to content Terraformation Tree Nursery at Future Forests Future Forests nursery facility Future Forests Nursery is the plant nursery for all of our Hawai’i restoration Most of our plant propagation is done by We collect seeds, process them and plant to match region and elevation as much as possible to maximize survival and growth rate of native The Future Forests Nursery also supports agroforestry and silviculture We grow tropical hardwood species that have high value and can provide overstory for economic crops in the Servic

Introducing BaseTen Tuhin Srivastava | May , Over the last decade, our team has used machine learning to solve problems across organizations big and small, all the way from framing problems and ideating to putting the power of models directly in the hands of We’ve seen amazing outcomes in healthcare, the creator economy, and business operations, and become convinced that machine learning is poised to have a profound impact on the way we live and We have also learned that it is still far too difficult to build product solutions that use machine learning for Despite the cost of training having rapidly decreased and the increased prevalence of effective pretrained models, the vast majority of gains are yet to be There are many things that are obviously difficult about doing machine learning today — gathering the right data, labeling data, training and optimizing models, and of course, and of course deploying and serving And a whole new set of impressive tools has emerged to tackle these However, in our experience, the stickiest part of modern ML work is shipping — and this crucial step is where most teams get It’s taking the model out of the notebook and embedding it in an internal or application such that real users can interact with it, give feedback, and ultimately make Shipping an ML product to end users isn t the last step in a linear It s a crucial part of an iterative loop -- only then can you establish the virtuous cycle you need to improve the performance of the model in the real Achieving this requires an immense amount of engineering work — grappling with web frameworks to serve the model, building the complex infrastructure to scale properly, and finally a completely separate stream of work to either integrate into existing systems or build new user All in all, it is still prohibitively expensive to go on solving real problems with machine learning and many talented teams are stuck in the “analytics” and “experimentation” phase of ML there is data and models, but few can point to outcomes such as better user experiences, more revenue or lesser Enter BaseTen BaseTen is the fastest way to build applications powered by machine Our mission is to increase the value delivered with machine learning by lowering the barrier to usable, productized Today, with BaseTen, data scientists can deploy machine learning models with a couple of lines of code and serve fast, scalable APIs without the infrastructure, framework, and deployment And you don’t have to be an ML practitioner to find BaseTen useful — engineers can choose from a library of models to bootstrap their machine learning It doesn’t stop there — if and when you need a user interface for your users, our builder lets you build stateful and interactive interfaces no experience Building a horizontal product with such a wide surface area has been challenging and A few guiding ideas that have helped pave the way for us are: Principle of least astonishment . BaseTen is a new way to build applications, but it should not seem Data scientists and engineers will notice concepts that match ones they’re already familiar Easy things are easy hard things are possible . Most use cases are dead simple, fast and scalable using That doesn’t come at the cost of control and visibility — BaseTen is architected modularly and is built using standard technologies (e.g. Docker, Knative, Postgres, etc), so more advanced users can have access to the underlying technologies when need Scale gracefully from toy apps to complex, applications . We expect that our users will build fun toy apps with However our sights are on supporting the development and operationalization of , applications with many creators and This goal enforces additional requirements on the product, including building statefulness as a This sets BaseTen apart from the app And we have seen promising signs from our alpha users: from a small data science team at a fintech company operationalizing a ML model without needing engineering resources, to a digital therapeutics startup with no ML practitioners creating a workflow application for their clinical operations team powered by a model from BaseTen’s model What excites us the most is the diversity of the use cases we’re seeing with our alpha We’re truly in the early innings of machine learning adoption and we’d love for you to be a part of it as What’s next Today, we’re excited to announce our Closed Beta — we’re opening up free access for early users to kick the tires and help shape our product All we d like from you is your If you d be interested in working with us during this period, please fill out this short form and tell us a little more about your use We re really excited about the coming weeks and months that we will get to work with you We re also shipping fast — some core areas we re focused in the short term: Expanded model zoo — over the past months we’ve added the most models (including Hu

Article Search: Follow : Delivering a Experience for the Worker from Anywhere in the World Axis Security Emerges from Stealth with $17 Million in Funding to Redefine Private Application Access Axis Security today emerged from stealth launching a , security and analytics platform that offers organizations simple and secure control of private application Built on a approach, the Axis Application Access Cloud offers a new agentless model that delivers the easiest and safest way to connect users on any device in minutes to private apps without touching the network or the Founded by Dor Knafo and Gil Azrielant, Axis Security has raised a total of $17 million in The initial investment came from Cyberstarts , a VC firm backed by founders and entrepreneurs from Sequoia Capital, Palo Alto Networks, Check Point, Imperva, among Ten Eleven Ventures Alex Doll led the Series A round in which Cyberstarts was the first Additional investors include Dan Amiga, founder of Fireglass, and board of director member Michael Fey, former president of Symantec and Blue The Axis Application Access Cloud solves the issue of implicitly open network access and removes the pain points of security associated with Virtual Private Networks (VPN s). VPN s can be complex, slow to deploy, hard to manage and inflexible, especially when it comes to providing access to supply chain partners, vendors, contractors, and remote "Axis Security is helping to solve one of the most complex security challenges for IT teams," said Dor Knafo, and "Enabling access to the basic tools of digital transformation should not be one of the biggest risks an organization We re giving IT teams what they ve been lacking when it comes to applications and that is a single managed solution for access, security, control, and scalability without the " "Axis Security is solving the problem of secure application access with a approach that keeps users separate from the network and the This dramatically reduces the attack surface, it also provides a level of visibility and control that is not found in alternative solutions Axis Security is helping organizations meet the needs of employees, partners, and vendors who require secure access to critical business applications anywhere, anytime," said Diego Souza, Managing Director, Security Technology, United "The exponential adoption of cloud technologies made secure access to private applications a top concern for Fortune companies," said Gili Raanan, general partner and founder for Cyberstarts and Sequoia Capital (Israel). "Dor and Gil s strong vision combined with their decision to blend top Israeli engineering talent with sales and marketing executives from Check Point, Tanium, Juniper, and McAfee set them up for " "Our business depends on globally located employees, contractors, and partners accessing enterprise applications," said Gram Ludlow, Chief Information Security "With new zero trust approaches that focus on secure application access, we are able to completely shift our strategy to securing our IT infrastructure, so that business can be accelerated, not brought to a This is the way of the " "For years, we ve been stating that identities are the new perimeter," said Curtis Simpson, Chief Information Security "This new zero trust solution from Axis offers a modern solution to a modern It enables organizations to truly monitor and manage risk and is a true enabler to move users from a generally flat network to a better, more secure experience with nothing more than an internet " Alex Doll, Founder and Managing General Partner, Ten Eleven Ventures commented, "The Application Access Cloud that Axis has developed gives enterprises the security solution they ve been looking for: unmatched visibility and control over users by requiring coordinated control over requests, users, policies, and We ve been very impressed by the innovative approach Axis has taken, as well as by how quickly the founding team has gone from concept to development to market It s a real testament to the magnitude of the challenge posed by the changing nature of enterprise networks and hybrid cloud usage, and the skill of the Axis team in solving it with an approach to modern application " "It is application access, not network access, that is a major pain point for organizations Business applications must be available anywhere, anytime, to any user, on any device," said John Grady, cybersecurity analyst at "This ‘Matrix of Anyness encompasses a myriad of constituencies, from employees to partners, a host of third parties, as well as cloud and Axis Security s , private application access solution separates users from applications, thus reducing the attack surface and providing greater control through

The less famous men were no less interesting: Henry Davison was a member of the Morgan & , chairman of the American Red Cross and League of Red Cross The Red Cross had privileged access to both sides of the Great War under their neutral Thomas Lamont was a member of JP Morgan & too, and the US Treasury s advisor to the American Peace Delegation in Paris (the negotiators of the Versailles Treaty). Both sides of the Federal Reserve partnership were represented in this Frank Vanderlip was a journalist who became president of the National City Bank (now Citibank). In between these positions he was Assistant Secretary of the US It was under Vanderlip s guidance that National City became the first American bank to expand overseas . He also created the International American Corporation: a banking conglomerate which had branches world wide by the end of the First World War . Vanderlip was also a trustee of the Carnegie Foundation for the Advancement of [2] Comedy The hearing was a political battle between senators concerned with American national interests and compromised illegal to have copies of the undisclosed text: the best information that the Senate had about the treaty was just one Associated Press Senator Henry Cabot Lodge volunteered to testify that he had seen a copy of the treaty in New York, but it was shown to him by a friend with absolutely no ties to financial Senator Lodge had never heard of anyone in finance ever seeing the He repeated this message several President Wilson wrote to the committee himself to reaffirm that unauthorized possession of the treaty in the US was against the This was interesting, seeing as his closest advisors were the source of the The Secretary of State Frank Lyon Polk asserted that all copies of the treaty legally in the United States were in his possession — specifically, they were locked in a safe in his office with the diplomatic seals Senator Elihu Root offered testimony The thrust of Senator Root s speech was to extol the munificence of Davison, and distance himself form this case of corporate
